Download Anaconda, Tensorflow, Pycharm
> : command prompt


#1. Anaconda
https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual
Check "Add Anaconda to the system PATH environment variable"
> conda                       //to check if it's installed.

tip^ When anaconda is installed, python is automatically installed.


#2. Tensorflow
> conda create --name tf     //make virtual environment
> active tf                  //active virtual environment
(tf)> conda install tensorflow


#3. Pycharm
https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/download/#section=windows

install Pycharm, and add to Anaconda
(File -> Setting -> Project: -> Interpreter -> Conda -> Existing environment)

print(tf.__version__)
